Class Satellite

java.lang.Object
SpaceObject
Satellite
All Implemented Interfaces:
Analyzable
public class Satellite extends SpaceObject implements Analyzable
The Satellite class represents a satellite in space. It is a subclass of SpaceObject and implements the Analyzable interface to allow for analytical operations.

    • Satellite

      public Satellite(int recordId, int noradId, String name, String country, String orbitType, String objectType, int launchYear, String launchSite, double longitude, double avgLongitude, String geoHash, int daysOld, int conjunctionCount)
      Constructs a new Satellite object with the specified attributes.
      Parameters:
      recordId - the unique identifier for the satellite
      noradId - the NORAD catalog number assigned to the satellite
      name - the name of the satellite
      country - the country of origin for the satellite
      orbitType - the type of orbit the satellite is in
      objectType - the type of object (in this case, "Payload")
      launchYear - the year the satellite was launched
      launchSite - the location from which the satellite was launched
      longitude - the current longitude of the satellite
      avgLongitude - the average longitude of the satellite
      geoHash - the geohash representing the location of the satellite
      daysOld - the number of days since the satellite was launched
      conjunctionCount - the number of recorded conjunctions
